Vendored Code and Bundled Third-Party Assets
--------------------------------------------

The repository includes third-party code and assets under vendor/. The components have been modified from their original versions for usage in this application. Those
components remain under their own licenses and are not relicensed by the Yagu
project notice above. Upstream license files are retained where included by the
upstream projects.

SharpSevenZip

- Path: vendor/SharpSevenZip/
- Authors: Joel Ahlgren, Markovtsev Vadim, Jérémy Ansel
- Copyright: Copyright (C) Markovtsev Vadim 2009, 2010, Jérémy Ansel 2024
- License: GNU Lesser General Public License v3.0 or later (LGPL-3.0-or-later)
- Source: https://github.com/JeremyAnsel/SharpSevenZip
- License file: vendor/SharpSevenZip/LICENSE

SharpSevenZip is a fork from Squid-Box.SevenZipSharp, which is a fork from
tomap's SevenZipSharp fork of the original CodePlex SevenZipSharp project.
Its README also notes that SharpSevenZipSfx uses an embedded SFX module by
Oleg Scherbakov.

7-Zip native binaries bundled through SharpSevenZip

- Paths:
  - vendor/SharpSevenZip/SharpSevenZip/SharpSevenZip/x64/7z.dll
  - vendor/SharpSevenZip/SharpSevenZip/SharpSevenZip/x86/7z.dll
- Product: 7-Zip 26.00
- Company: Igor Pavlov
- Copyright: Copyright (c) 1999-2026 Igor Pavlov
- Upstream project and license information: https://www.7-zip.org/license.txt

For 7z.dll, the upstream 7-Zip license information states that the licenses are:

- GNU LGPL as the main license for most of the code.
- GNU LGPL with the unRAR license restriction for some code.
- BSD 3-clause License for some code.
- BSD 2-clause License for some code.

Additional copyright and attribution notices from the upstream 7-Zip license
information include:

- LZFSE data decompression code derived from Apple's LZFSE compression library:
  Copyright (c) 2015-2016, Apple Inc. All rights reserved.
- ZSTD data decompression code developed using Facebook's original zstd decoder
  code as reference code: Copyright (c) Facebook, Inc. All rights reserved.
- BSD-licensed 7-Zip code portions: Copyright (c) 2023-2025 Igor Pavlov.
- XXH64 code derived from original XXH64 code developed by Yann Collet:
  Copyright (c) 2012-2021 Yann Collet; Copyright (c) 2023-2025 Igor Pavlov.
- RAR decompression support uses source code from the unRAR program. All
  copyrights to original unRAR code are owned by Alexander Roshal.

The unRAR source license restriction reproduced by 7-Zip is:

The unRAR sources cannot be used to re-create the RAR compression algorithm,
which is proprietary. Distribution of modified unRAR sources in separate form
or as a part of other software is permitted, provided that it is clearly stated
in the documentation and source comments that the code may not be used to
develop a RAR (WinRAR) compatible archiver.

